<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870415-0106 </DOCNO><HL> Griffith Consumers Purchase</HL><DD> 04/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FUELTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CHEVERLY, Md.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Griffith Consumers Co. agreed to buy the stock of closely held Carl King Inc. for about $14 million.    King, a Camden, Del., gasoline and heating oil marketer, had revenue of $56 million and net income of $1 million in fiscal 1986, which ended Sept. 30. Griffith is a retail distributor of petroleum products. For the six months ended Dec. 31, Griffith had a net loss of $119,669 on revenue of $16.9 million.    The sale is expected to be completed April 30. </TEXT></DOC>